Gunin and Nirmit ‚Äì co-founders of Ritivel. TL;DR Ritivel is an AI-native workspace for regulatory and medical writing teams at life sciences companies. Our AI agents draft CTDs

delays treatment for thousands of patients who need it. Yet regulatory teams are stuck in a painful
months-long process to create FDA submissions like CTDs
and BLAs: 1. Information overload üìö These submissions require synthesizing thousands of pages of clinical data

and chasing colleagues for the right files. 3. Endless follow-ups üìß Regulatory leads spend their days sending reminder emails
and managing status updates across teams. 4. Manual drafting bottlenecks ‚è≥ Even with all the information gathered

our agents automatically source the right documents from across your organization: no more digging through folders or chasing down files. Automated follow-ups üìß Integrated with Outlook

astrophysics research @ PrincetonCompany LaunchesCorelayer: AI on-call engineer for data pipelinesSee original launch postHey everyone! üëã We‚Äôre Mitch and Shipra - before Corelayer

we built data infrastructure at Goldman Sachs where we spent many late nights and weekends debugging systems that processed 100s of billions of rows a day. TL;DR When you‚Äôre on call in data-heavy industries like fintech

you need to inspect data to debug production issues. We built a platform that monitors both data and infrastructure for anomalies and uses AI agents to debug and suggest fixes in minutes. Corelayer Launch Video On-call support is painful and expensive All engineers hate being on call. Production issues kill velocity

and become more and more costly as companies scale. Fortune 100s spend $100M+/year on first-line-of-defense production support. Smaller companies can‚Äôt afford to burn scarce engineering resources on time-consuming support and maintenance. The (sensitive) data problem If you‚Äôre a backend engineer at a fintech
you probably own a service that queries data
a data pipeline). When this service is running in production

you‚Äôll see two failure modes: Exceptions in logs and/or failing jobs Bad data produced by your service ‚ÄúBad data‚Äù can mean anything from incorrect values to entirely missing or duplicated rows. This is really common in certain products and industries
but you‚Äôre totally blind to these errors without monitoring data for anomalies and querying data while debugging. In regulated environments where this problem is prevalent
which is another constraint we have to solve for. Corelayer solves this We continuously monitor logs
and data for anomalies and use AI agents to debug

and suggest fixes for issues. We also filter out false positives and group related issues to reduce alert noise. Every team is different. We take feedback from human engineers so our agents learn your systems and improve over time. Data is especially sensitive in regulated industries. We‚Äôre SOC 2 compliant
offer on-prem deployments and confidential compute (hardware-backed secure environments)

and expose an audit trail of each step performed by the agent with citations. Our Asks Does your team deal with data or integrations and spend more time on production support than you‚Äôd like? Let‚Äôs chat. Can you connect us with an engineering leader at a finserv

or insurance company? Reach out at founders@corelayer.com. Thank you!
